A family in Zimmerman area of Kasarani can now breathe a sigh of relief after their missing 12-year-old child was found safe and sound. Stacey Wambui was spotted by a Good Samaritan abandoned at Githurai area at around 9pm yesterday. Meanwhile, police have arrested two lovers linked to the disappearance of children in the area. They say the two are assisting in solving the puzzle that has gone on for almost a month now. Tears of Joy flowed freely on the cheeks of parents and neighbours who joined in celebrating the news of the return of 12-year-old Stacey Wambui who went missing on Thursday—the agonising FOUR days of searching for the girl ending on a good note. Stacey reportedly went missing after a woman showed up, greeted her while playing outside their home—she would follow the mysterious woman to a food joint near the area where she was bought chips—she found herself in a lodging in Githurai 45 area The Grade 4 learner was later discovered by a Good Samaritan after she was abandoned by the woman—she was stranded and crying when the Good Samaritan took her to an AP police post This comes as police say they have arrested two main suspects in connection with the disappearance of children in the area—the two lovers are being held and questioned as investigations to unravel the crimes intensify Focus has shifted to the search for others who are still missing. Among them Frankline Gicheru who went missing on Tuesday this week, Abraham Nhial who has been missing since the 3rd of this month, Joy Waithera who has been missing for Three weeks, among others. Zimmerman residents still wary of what has become a dangerous place to live. Video Of The Day: KEMRI scientists examine safety of anti-malarial drugs in first trimester of pregnancy